{Syntax:}\par slopeat(Segment, Point) or slopeat(Line, Point) or slopeat(Ray, Point)\par
\par Displays, with a legend, the value of the slope of the segment, ray, or line (Line may be a tangent, bisector, etc.) at the location Point in Plot view.\par
{\par Example:}\par slopeat(line(point(0,1), point(3,2)),point(-10,4)) places "sline(point(0,1),point(3,2)=1/3" at the point (-10,4) in Plot view\par }